statement.p:
          Let p(x) = \sqrt{x}, q(x) = \frac{1}{x},and r(x) = x^3. Express each of the following as a transformation of p, q, or r. For instance, y = \sqrt{ \left( x+1 \right) + 2 } can be expressed as y = p\left( x + 1 \right) + 2.


y = 1 + \frac{1}{x}

y = 8x^3

y = \frac{1}{2x - 2}

y = \sqrt{6 - x}

y = 3 - \sqrt{x}

y = \left( 2x \right)^3

Sketch a graph of each piecewise-defined function.




      f(x) =
      \begin{cases}
          x, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ x \geq -2 \\
          \lvert x \rvert, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ x \lt -2 \\
      \end{cases}






      f(x) =
      \begin{cases}
          x^3, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ x \lt 0 \\
          2^x, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ x \geq 0 \\
      \end{cases}






      f(x) =
      \begin{cases}
          x + 2, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ x \leq 0 \\
          2, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ 0 \lt x \lt 4 \\
          \sqrt{x}, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ x \gt 4 \\
      \end{cases}






      f(x) =
      \begin{cases}
          1, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ \lvert x \rvert \lt 1 \\
          x^2, \amp  \ \text{if}  \ \lvert x \rvert \geq 1 \\
      \end{cases}
